to .)  (perhaps, appropriately modified in the infrared domain).
In Sect.  we discuss an example - two-dimensional
Yang-Mills theory.
It enjoyed considerable numerical support from lattice
simulations. It is also obtained in the lattice strong
coupling () expansion.    

