The factor  occurs at the stage of division of the reducible representation
into two irreducible, .
This separation is irrelevant for our purposes.
The 1-string attraction (per unit length)
is determined by exchanges that are localized in space
on the scale .
How the middle parts of the long  1-strings interact is independent
on  details of endpoints which are separated
from the middle part by distance  
 - whether the quarks are symmetrized or antisymmetrized
with respect to color, or none, does not matter.
It must depend only on -ality. In the general case of the -string
the quadratic Casimir is
C_R = kN + _i r_i^2 - _i c_i^2 - k^2 N ,
where  and  are the lengths of the rows and the columns, respectively,
of the Young tableau of the representation . As we 
have argued above for the -string, in  the general
case the string tension should depend only on the 
-ality and not on the specific representation - hence, it cannot depend
on  or  which  lead to  potential  dependences. 

