Appendix 


In this appendix we calculate the distance where two 1-strings merge
into a 2-string (see Fig. b). Let us denote the angle between the two
1-strings by . Then the forces on the junction yield
_2 = 2_1 .
Assuming the sine formula dsf  for the string tension, we obtain
 which is physically reasonable: 
in the large  limit the two strings
hardly interact, and the "merging angle" should vanish.

Comparing the energy of the two separate 1-strings (Fig. ) with the
energy of the configuration in Fig. b we arrive at 
2_1 L = 4_1  l2   + _2 ( L-l2  ). 
Now, by substituting the sine formula dsf  and the angle 
 we obtain
L( 1-N ) = l (2-N   2N    ).
Thus, in the large  limit, the critical distance is
l = L  ^3 N^3 .
